               <join result="criminalCharge" id="t18440408-1281-charge-2" targOrder="Y" targets="def2-1281-18440408 t18440408-1281-offence-1 t18440408-1281-verdict-2"></join>
               <p>1281. <persName id="def1-1281-18440408" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def1-1281-18440408" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1281-18440408" type="age" value="17"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1281-18440408" type="surname" value="WATTS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def1-1281-18440408" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">WILLIAM WATTS</hi>
                  </persName> and <persName id="def2-1281-18440408" type="defendantName">
                     <interp inst="def2-1281-18440408" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1281-18440408" type="age" value="17"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1281-18440408" type="surname" value="DANIELS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="def2-1281-18440408" type="given" value="STEPHEN"></interp>
                     <hi rend="largeCaps">STEPHEN DANIELS</hi>
                  </persName> were indicted for<rs id="t18440408-1281-offence-1" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18440408-1281-offence-1" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18440408-1281-offence-1" type="offenceSubcategory" value="theftFromPlace"></interp> ripping and cutting 198lbs. weight of lead, the goods of <persName id="t18440408-name-1372" type="victimName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1372" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1372" type="surname" value="HOPPE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1372" type="given" value="JOSEPH"></interp>
                        <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18440408-1281-offence-1 t18440408-name-1372"></join>Joseph Hoppe</persName>, with intent to steal it.—2nd <hi rend="smallCaps">COUNT</hi>, for stealing the same lead, being fixed.</rs>
               </p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1373" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1373" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1373" type="surname" value="BONE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1373" type="given" value="THOMAS"></interp>THOMAS BONE</persName>
                  </hi>. I live in Adam and Eve-court, Whitecross-street. I went to the top of the house at eight o'clock in the evening, and saw the prisoner Watts on the roof—he ran along—I saw the lead of the gutter all doubled up—there were four cuts in it, but it was not wholly cut off—it was doubled up from the coping—it was Mr. Joseph Hoppe's house.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined by</hi> 
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">MR. CHARNOCK</hi> 
                  <hi rend="italic">Q.</hi> It was not your house? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> No,</p>
               <xptr type="pageFacsimile" doc="184404080212"></xptr>
               <p>I live at No. 9, and this was next door—it is an old house—it was dark, but I had a candle in my hand.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1374" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1374" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1374" type="surname" value="HOOKER"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1374" type="given" value="WILLIAM"></interp>WILLIAM HOOKER</persName>
                  </hi>. I live at No. 13, Adam and Eve-court. At half-past eight o'clock that night I went through my trap door to the top of my house—I saw Daniels in the corner of the gutter, and asked what he did there—he said, "Pray forgive me this time, I will never come here any more"—I took him to the trap door to take him down—he insisted on going down first, and when he got down he took away the ladder and left me there—I found the lead was cut and rolled up from the coping and the tiles.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> How many months before had you been up there? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> I may have been there about six weeks ago—I do not know whether Daniels removed the ladder by accident—he did move it, and I dropped down—the lead was entirely separated from the other.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1375" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1375" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1375" type="surname" value="HAYWARD"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1375" type="given" value="JAMES"></interp>JAMES HAYWARD</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman.</hi>) I saw Watts drop from a shed about seven houses from Bones' in Adam and Eve-court—he was endeavouring to conceal this knife, and dropped it behind him—I asked him where he fell from—he said, "From the top here," pointing up—he was stunned.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <persName id="t18440408-name-1376" type="witnessName">
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1376" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1376" type="surname" value="LEE"></interp>
                        <interp inst="t18440408-name-1376" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>HENRY LEE</persName>
                  </hi> (<hi rend="italic">policeman.</hi>) I saw the lead—it was cut off so that it could have been carried away without using a knife again—the cutting appeared to be quite fresh.</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="italic">Cross-examined. Q.</hi> Can you swear whether it was cut a week or ten days before? <hi rend="italic">A.</hi> It was quite fresh—to the best of my belief it was cut at that very time—it was cut away, and the coping of the wall was taken off—the lead was rolled up and entirely cut off from the other. (Watts received a good character.)</p>
               <p>
                  <hi rend="largeCaps">WATTS</hi>—<hi rend="smallCaps">
                     <rs id="t18440408-1281-verdict-1" type="verdictDescription">
